# Trivy Ignore File - DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT ONLY
#
# These security findings are INTENTIONALLY ACCEPTED for the dev environment
# to balance security with developer productivity.
#
# ⚠️  DO NOT copy this file to staging or production environments!

###############################################################################
# EKS Public Access - Development Only
###############################################################################

# AVD-AWS-0040: Public cluster access is enabled
# Justification: Dev environment requires kubectl access from developer machines
# Mitigation: Use VPN or restrict to office IPs in terraform.tfvars for added security
# Production: MUST set endpoint_public_access = false and use bastion/VPN
AVD-AWS-0040

# AVD-AWS-0041: Cluster allows access from 0.0.0.0/0
# Justification: Simplifies developer access without VPN setup
# Mitigation: Developers can override public_access_cidrs in terraform.tfvars
# Production: MUST specify restricted CIDR ranges or disable public access
AVD-AWS-0041

###############################################################################
# VPC Configuration - Standard Multi-AZ Setup
###############################################################################

# AVD-AWS-0104: VPC endpoint security group allows egress
# Justification: VPC endpoints need HTTPS egress to AWS services within VPC
# This is limited to VPC CIDR, not internet egress
AVD-AWS-0164

# AVD-AWS-0164: Public subnets with public IP assignment
# Justification: Required for NAT Gateway and Application Load Balancers
# Private subnets (where workloads run) do not have public IPs
AVD-AWS-0164
